cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LG

Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of inclusion between sets of traces recognized by data automata, which involves concepts from logic (e.g., automata theory, model checking) and programming languages (e.g., variables, data domains). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also presents a semi-algorithm based on abstraction refinement, which involves techniques from programming languages (e.g., abstract interpretation, refinement) and formal methods (e.g., verification, synthesis). Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions the implementation of a prototype tool, which involves concepts from data structures (e.g., algorithms, data types) and machine learning (e.g., experimental evaluation). Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible categories.
